  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enabling timely response to critical events and reinforcing non-violent and conciliatory approach to justice in the Bangsamoro</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Enable the deployment of timely actions that harness traditional, formal, and hybrid institutions and arrangements to resolve disputes and prevent violent conflict, including violent extremism. 
2. Generate empirical evidence about the emergence and dynamics of violent extremism to help prevent the spread of radicalization into extremist groups.
3. Reduce tensions and reinforce non-violent and conciliatory measures in the Bangsamoro using a restorative justice approach.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To strengthen legitimate and conflict-sensitive institutions that promote peace and reconciliation among communities in the Bangsamoro to break the cycle of violent conflict that could undermine the transition.</narrative>
  </description>
